# Simulation and Computational Notes

## Assumptions

- Earth is treated as a rotating sphere centered on its polar axis
- Mass is symmetrically distributed unless stated
- Orbital and rotational forces are vector-decomposed

## Tools Suggested

- Python with SciPy / NumPy for numerical calculations
- Matplotlib / Plotly for polar and spherical plots
- Unity or Blender for 3D visual simulations

## Output Goals

- Simulated gravitational field lines under time-curvature
- Visuals of Earth’s field shape over seasons
- Variations of energy density by latitude 
